Texts.Eng: A secure cupboard to store your belongings.
Texts.Chs: 一个安全的柜子来存放你的物品。

Texts.Eng: Floran staresss at cupboard. Cupboard doesn't open. Floran disappointed.
Texts.Chs: 叶族人盯着橱柜。柜子打不开。叶族人失望了。

Texts.Eng: I'm sure this cupboard will hold all of my belongings.
Texts.Chs: 我相信这个柜子能装下我所有的东西。

Texts.Eng: Pretty neat design, but I prefer my cupboards to not look like garage doors.
Texts.Chs: 设计相当整洁，但我更喜欢我的橱柜，不要看起来像车库门。

Texts.Eng: This cupboard is built to be sturdy not only to store our personal belongings, but also heavy weaponry and armors.
Texts.Chs: 这个柜子不仅坚固耐用，可以存放我们的个人物品，还可以存放重型武器和盔甲。

Texts.Eng: This cupboard looks extraordinarily sturdy. Is this really necessary?
Texts.Chs: 这个柜子看起来特别结实。这真的有必要吗？

Texts.Eng: This cupboard looks sturdy and safe. I can keep my belongings in here without worrying.
Texts.Chs: 这个柜子看起来坚固而安全。我可以把我的东西放在这里而不用担心。

Texts.Eng: What a weird cupboard. Never seen any cupboards like this.
Texts.Chs: 多奇怪的柜子啊。从没见过这样的橱柜。

Texts.Eng: While it's not a design I'd have chosed, my belongings will surely be safe in there.
Texts.Chs: 虽然这不是我会选择的设计，但我的物品在里面肯定是安全的。
